9
00:00:47,732 --> 00:00:48,812
What is accessibility?

10
00:00:49,569 --> 00:00:54,390
I consider accessibility the correction of a mismatch between a person and their environment.

11
00:00:54,870 --> 00:00:56,750
This is more than just disability.

12
00:00:56,810 --> 00:01:02,751
This includes things like if a tall person can't fit in an airplane seat, well, they

13
00:01:02,811 --> 00:01:04,192
have an accessibility problem.

14
00:01:04,792 --> 00:01:09,573
Or if a deaf person needs captions in order to follow something, that's also an accessibility

15
00:01:09,593 --> 00:01:09,933
problem.

16
00:01:10,353 --> 00:01:13,433
I happen to be deaf, so that one's pretty near and dear to my heart.

17
00:01:14,453 --> 00:01:18,174
In general, if settings are not accessible, then they may as well not exist.

18
00:01:19,137 --> 00:01:24,243
So for a game such as Madden, we have added in the concept of a welcome screen.

19
00:01:24,884 --> 00:01:31,192
This means that as soon as you get into the game, as soon as the game boots, before it's even fully

20
00:01:31,252 --> 00:01:36,758
installed, there's a settings screen that lets you turn on all the really important settings.

21
00:01:37,219 --> 00:01:38,540
for people with disabilities.

22
00:01:39,260 --> 00:01:40,621
This can include volume control,

23
00:01:40,661 --> 00:01:42,983
this can include the in-game communication

24
00:01:43,063 --> 00:01:44,545
things we'll be talking about today.

25
00:01:44,565 --> 00:01:46,947
And this allows people

26
00:01:46,987 --> 00:01:48,568
to turn on the settings they need

27
00:01:48,728 --> 00:01:49,969
before the game even begins.

28
00:01:50,530 --> 00:01:52,691
And I can tell you from a captioning perspective

29
00:01:53,152 --> 00:01:54,933
how important that is, because I have sat

30
00:01:54,953 --> 00:01:56,194
through many intros of games

31
00:01:56,695 --> 00:01:58,476
and not have been able to turn on captioning

32
00:01:58,596 --> 00:02:00,658
until well later in the game

33
00:02:00,678 --> 00:02:01,559
and by then I'm lost.

34
00:02:02,270 --> 00:02:04,091
This is true of all settings.

35
00:02:04,571 --> 00:02:07,394
It's really, really important that they're there from the very beginning.

36
00:02:08,434 --> 00:02:11,136
And if you're wondering, why even have an accessibility menu?

37
00:02:11,557 --> 00:02:15,820
Well, it's true that technically all user settings are accessibility settings.

38
00:02:16,380 --> 00:02:18,862
However, especially when it comes to early install,

39
00:02:19,342 --> 00:02:22,185
not all of those settings will always be available.

40
00:02:22,825 --> 00:02:24,266
So for the case of Madden,

41
00:02:24,987 --> 00:02:30,869
Every setting we considered super important for that type of scenario, we had gathered up into

42
00:02:30,889 --> 00:02:35,331
the accessibility settings screen. Now, some of those settings are actually in other screens as

43
00:02:35,391 --> 00:02:40,474
well, such as volume control. But this means we can guarantee that those settings are available

44
00:02:40,614 --> 00:02:45,356
in a wide variety of places at any given point in time without having to worry about any other

45
00:02:45,496 --> 00:02:49,478
technical complication. So, it greatly simplified the problem formatting in particular.

